1
00:00:08,910 --> 00:00:10,170
(This drama is based on
the 2018 cryptocurrency market.)

2
00:00:10,170 --> 00:00:11,540
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

3
00:00:11,540 --> 00:00:12,780
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

4
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:17,980
What are you doing over there?

5
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:21,580
The view here is
absolutely incredible.

6
00:00:22,590 --> 00:00:24,420
Having some coffee with this view...

7
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:26,290
would be just perfect.

8
00:00:28,590 --> 00:00:31,130
Da Hee, you want to have coffee
with me at a time like this?

9
00:00:33,060 --> 00:00:34,060
Why?

10
00:00:34,430 --> 00:00:36,630
Don't you have any questions for me?

11
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:38,230
I just don't get it.

12
00:00:38,230 --> 00:00:39,770
Why on earth would Da Hee do that?

13
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,270
You know Assistant Manager Kwak
from the PR Team?

14
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:45,740
A friend of his used to work
at the same company as Da Hee.

15
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:48,910
She also got caught
bashing people online back then.

16
00:00:48,910 --> 00:00:49,950
It caused a huge uproar.

17
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:51,780
I had no idea.

18
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:54,150
I was saying no one's as tight-lipped
as our Da Hee,

19
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:56,350
and I told her all my secrets.

20
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:58,450
You think you're the only one,
Seung Jae?

21
00:00:59,820 --> 00:01:00,820
Mr. Ko.

22
00:01:06,630 --> 00:01:08,630
Why did she use "Hoppang" for an ID?

23
00:01:08,630 --> 00:01:10,730
Not sliced, garlic, or pizza bread.
Why hoppang, of all things?

24
00:01:10,930 --> 00:01:12,370
Is that what you're curious about?

25
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:15,340
You see, with hoppang,
a steamed bun,

26
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:18,810
you can't know its true flavor
with just one bite.

27
00:01:19,710 --> 00:01:22,750
Because the red bean filling
is hidden deep inside.

28
00:01:23,580 --> 00:01:24,850
I'm the same way.

29
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:28,650
If I smile and act all friendly
on the outside,

30
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:32,260
people just assume
that's all there is to me.

31
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,120
Like a bunch of fools.

32
00:01:34,790 --> 00:01:37,660
Are you calling those
who trusted you a fool right now?

33
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,400
That's just malicious.

34
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,700
"Malicious?"

35
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:47,800
Then, since it's come to this,

36
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:50,110
how about I get truly malicious...

37
00:01:50,540 --> 00:01:52,510
and tell you one more lie?

38
00:01:53,410 --> 00:01:54,440
What?

39
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:56,810
I mean,

40
00:01:57,550 --> 00:02:01,150
it's possible I had my own sob story
about why I had no other choice.

41
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:05,760
For example, I'm a psychopath
who can't read people.

42
00:02:05,820 --> 00:02:07,320
Shut it.

43
00:02:07,890 --> 00:02:08,890
Or...

44
00:02:09,230 --> 00:02:11,930
an alien who's here
to throw the world into chaos?

45
00:02:12,230 --> 00:02:14,800
- Or if not that...
- Still talking, are we?

46
00:02:15,330 --> 00:02:17,530
Or that I was abandoned
by my parents.

47
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:21,740
What?

48
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:27,240
- Does "sorry" fix everything?
- An abandoned kid.

49
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,310
What will a child like that
amount to?

50
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:32,050
Who'd want a kid who wasn't sweet
and never smiled?

51
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:35,420
I was adopted
and sent back several times.

52
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:39,290
As I kept returning
to the orphanage,

53
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:41,360
I slowly started
to realize something.

54
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:47,400
Oh, maybe...

55
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,400
the real me just wasn't good enough.

56
00:02:51,670 --> 00:02:53,200
Who wears those these days?

57
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:56,510
I hoped things would be different
when I grew up, but...

58
00:02:57,170 --> 00:02:59,010
- Seriously.
- I know, right?

59
00:03:02,350 --> 00:03:05,210
Excuse me, I think that's my seat.

60
00:03:09,090 --> 00:03:10,190
But it was exactly the same.

61
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:13,920
An office isn't
just a place for work.

62
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:16,160
You have to know how to get along
with people.

63
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:19,200
Especially a pretty girl like you.

64
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:20,930
Why are you like this?

65
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:23,330
That doubt I'd had
since I was a child...

66
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,570
- You got that, right?
- was confirmed...

67
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:26,100
when I started work.

68
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:28,970
- "So it's true."
- Yes.

69
00:03:28,970 --> 00:03:30,840
"I shouldn't live as my true self."

70
00:03:32,710 --> 00:03:34,040
From then on,

71
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:37,510
I lived my life as a Jung Da Hee
people would like.

72
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:41,680
Acting nice, acting sweet,
and always smiling.

73
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,720
- But at some point,
- Da Hee.

74
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:46,120
- it started to feel so unfair.
- About Mr. Lee...

75
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:48,830
He told people you two were a thing.

76
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:52,400
What? That's not true at all.

77
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:55,330
And you know Ji Min from
the Management Support Division?

78
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,130
Isn't she the worst?

79
00:03:57,130 --> 00:03:59,400
- Did you see what she was wearing?
- I lived my life wearing a mask...

80
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,070
- She is so tactless.
- and hid who I was.

81
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:05,010
So when I see people living freely,
showing their true colors,

82
00:04:05,910 --> 00:04:07,510
it's nauseating,
and it makes me angry.

83
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:18,290
So that's how I coped,
by letting off steam in my own way.

84
00:04:18,890 --> 00:04:22,290
(What's wrong with that person
from the AE Team?)

85
00:04:25,460 --> 00:04:28,660
It didn't actually
solve anything, though.

86
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:36,240
Besides, secrets don't stay secret
for long anyway.

87
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:38,880
When my cover was blown,
I'd just move to a new company,

88
00:04:38,910 --> 00:04:40,010
over and over.

89
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:43,210
I repeated that same, tedious act.

90
00:04:44,950 --> 00:04:48,280
Then one day, miraculously,
I met someone.

91
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,650
Someone just like me.

92
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:54,160
She was sitting
in a transparent chair,

93
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,630
and I was wearing
a transparent mask.

94
00:04:57,490 --> 00:05:00,930
The way she tried so desperately
to fit in...

95
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:02,870
was so much like me.

96
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:06,670
I couldn't get her out of my head.

97
00:05:06,670 --> 00:05:07,700
Da Hae.

98
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:09,870
But she just wouldn't
give me an opening.

99
00:05:09,970 --> 00:05:11,610
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

100
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:15,780
I'd purposely get her Americanos,
knowing well she hated them.

101
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:17,250
Wait a minute.

102
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:18,510
You did that on purpose?

103
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:21,680
You knew I didn't like it,
and you did that on purpose?

104
00:05:21,820 --> 00:05:22,890
Why?

105
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:27,560
So I'd have an excuse to apologize
and treat you to a meal.

106
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:30,760
Gosh, you're really messed up,
aren't you?

107
00:05:31,090 --> 00:05:34,600
You should have just stayed
Ms. Round, a roly-poly, then.

108
00:05:35,130 --> 00:05:36,130
What?

109
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:38,370
Just like what a roly-poly is
meant to do,

110
00:05:38,830 --> 00:05:41,970
you should've rolled around
and gotten stuck in a corner.

111
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:44,710
Why did you
suddenly have to take flight?

112
00:05:45,540 --> 00:05:47,110
When you do that,

113
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,980
it makes me want to lash out.

114
00:05:55,790 --> 00:05:58,090
I feel like saying,
"You're no better than I am."

115
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:01,060
"Stop trying so hard
and just fall apart with me."

116
00:06:01,890 --> 00:06:03,830
I just get this urge to rattle you.

117
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:06,100
Fall apart with you? How?

118
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:09,500
What was I supposed to do?
Post nasty comments with you online?

119
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:13,600
That would've been nice,

120
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:17,310
but do you think people
would've let you get away with it?

121
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:22,510
All those people who genuinely care
about you and love you.

122
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:25,410
Do you think they'd have stood by
and watched you fall apart?

123
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:31,650
Okay, I get it.

124
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:37,430
- I get it, okay? So come down...
- No.

125
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,900
If I go down now,

126
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,730
I'll have to smile...

127
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:45,100
and say it was all
a misunderstanding...

128
00:06:45,970 --> 00:06:47,470
and lie all over again.

129
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:50,970
I don't want to do that anymore.

130
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:53,640
And I have no reason to.

131
00:06:58,010 --> 00:06:59,150
So, this is it.

132
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:05,150
This is it?

133
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:06,490
This is it?

134
00:07:06,490 --> 00:07:07,860
- Are you sure?
- What are you doing?

135
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:09,030
Let go of me!

136
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:11,830
Do you really need me to give you
a reason not to die?

137
00:07:12,230 --> 00:07:14,730
If you die on a Friday like today,

138
00:07:14,730 --> 00:07:16,200
Darn it! Let go of me!

139
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,930
people will go to your weekend wake!

140
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,270
What did you just say?

141
00:07:19,470 --> 00:07:20,970
A weekend funeral
for your coworkers...

142
00:07:20,970 --> 00:07:21,970
when they have to rest?

143
00:07:21,970 --> 00:07:23,040
Are you out of your mind?

144
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:27,440
I'd have to get my black clothes
dry-cleaned, just for you!

145
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:30,110
- That hurts!
- Exactly!

146
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,280
So don't die and live.

147
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:37,350
Live and fight through it!

148
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:39,320
You never know.

149
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:41,290
Things can change.

150
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:44,160
You might even find the courage
to change things.

151
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:48,130
A moment like that
could come for you too!

152
00:07:57,140 --> 00:08:01,280
(Episode 12: To the Moon)

153
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,280
(Kang Eun Sang)

154
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:08,480
By the way, Ji Hye,
did you check the delivery?

155
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,920
Yes, I checked it first thing
when I got in.

156
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:13,360
But I heard some items were missing.

157
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:14,660
What?

158
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:17,260
About that... Just a moment.

159
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,860
If they report missing items,

160
00:08:19,860 --> 00:08:21,930
call the logistics center
right away.

161
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:25,330
- Here's the number.
- Okay. I'm sorry.

162
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:29,770
Ji Hye, what did you do
before working here?

163
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:35,180
I worked part-time
while I was job hunting.

164
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:37,210
Gosh, that must have been tough.

165
00:08:37,210 --> 00:08:39,580
Juggling work and job hunting.

166
00:08:40,650 --> 00:08:43,420
Let's both give it our all.

167
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:48,160
The handover period is short,
so I feel a little rushed myself.

168
00:08:48,590 --> 00:08:50,760
Yes, I'll do my absolute best.

169
00:08:54,530 --> 00:08:55,930
If you look here...

170
00:08:57,230 --> 00:08:59,200
(Annual Leave Request Form,
Kim Ji Song, Accounting Team)

171
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:02,940
(Reason: China trip to research
snack trends and market structure)

172
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:06,180
Yes.

173
00:09:06,710 --> 00:09:07,710
Really.

174
00:09:08,740 --> 00:09:10,010
I mean it.

175
00:09:11,210 --> 00:09:13,620
What? Why am I thinking of that now,
of all times?

176
00:09:42,010 --> 00:09:44,510
Ji Song. About those copies
we talked about...

177
00:09:44,580 --> 00:09:46,080
(Annual Leave Request Form)

178
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:47,680
Are you taking time off?

179
00:09:48,050 --> 00:09:51,150
- Are you going somewhere?
- To China.

180
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:53,490
I have to do some field research.

181
00:09:53,620 --> 00:09:56,230
Time off? Are you kidding?
We're slammed.

182
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:59,160
- What? But I...
- "But?"

183
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,960
Are you getting back
with your foreign boyfriend?

184
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:05,840
Why? Going to China
to get up to something again?

185
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:08,900
That's not it.
I have my own personal reasons...

186
00:10:08,970 --> 00:10:09,970
Exactly!

187
00:10:10,810 --> 00:10:12,710
We're busy right now,
so put in your request another time.

188
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:16,210
Yes, I understand.

189
00:10:24,590 --> 00:10:26,590
So Ji Song didn't get
her time off, then?

190
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:31,630
Yes, she wanted to go to China
to learn to make tanghulu herself.

191
00:10:32,190 --> 00:10:35,630
Since she couldn't go, she's decided
to practice on her own today.

192
00:10:35,730 --> 00:10:38,730
Wait, but why on earth
is she practicing at the office?

193
00:10:38,830 --> 00:10:39,900
Oh, my.

194
00:10:40,170 --> 00:10:43,370
She said she burned a pot at home,
and you almost killed her.

195
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:46,580
Gosh, she completely scraped up
the bottom of the pot.

196
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,180
Goodness.

197
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:50,550
She's best buds with
the maintenance guy, you know.

198
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:52,350
He said it was fine
if she cleaned up afterward.

199
00:10:52,450 --> 00:10:55,950
Gosh, she's got a long way to go.

200
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,560
Anyway, where are we going
right now?

201
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:01,720
We're not going far.

202
00:11:02,830 --> 00:11:04,090
We're going to a karaoke bar.

203
00:11:04,490 --> 00:11:06,000
- Karaoke?
- Yes.

204
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:15,670
<i>Oh, what a beautiful day</i>

205
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:19,880
<i>Even the sun and the moon</i>
<i>are on my side</i>

206
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,680
<i>Shining just for me</i>

207
00:11:23,010 --> 00:11:24,250
<i>Oh, come...</i>

208
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:27,950
Hey, what's wrong?

209
00:11:28,050 --> 00:11:31,290
Hey, we've only sung Dr. Ham's songs
for two hours.

210
00:11:31,290 --> 00:11:32,820
Isn't that enough?

211
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:35,690
We got a perfect score 12 times!

212
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:36,830
Is that still not enough for you?

213
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:39,500
It's not enough.

214
00:11:40,660 --> 00:11:41,930
It's not enough.

215
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,500
I need more of Dr. Ham.

216
00:11:46,870 --> 00:11:50,510
Eun Sang,
I'm having such a hard time.

217
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:54,380
I miss Dr. Ham so much.

218
00:11:56,310 --> 00:12:00,520
How do I get through this?
What do I do?

219
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,320
Do you...

220
00:12:04,550 --> 00:12:07,260
want me to tell you
how to get over it?

221
00:12:07,690 --> 00:12:08,720
Yes.

222
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:12,930
You have to accept it.

223
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,400
That you can't get over it.

224
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:20,370
What?

225
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:25,140
Did you think you could just skip
the pain and hardship,

226
00:12:25,210 --> 00:12:27,010
like you're skipping an ad
on YouTube?

227
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:31,950
You have to take it all in,
with every fiber of your being.

228
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:36,650
You must endure that agonizing pain
and see it through.

229
00:12:38,390 --> 00:12:40,820
And if you do that,
eventually, it might get a little...

230
00:12:42,390 --> 00:12:43,830
Better?

231
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:47,000
I guess it gets better?

232
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:51,370
So does it get better or not?

233
00:12:51,430 --> 00:12:52,970
I don't know.

234
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,240
Everyone says it'll get better.

235
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,610
But I'm not so sure.

236
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:02,810
I've never considered getting better
in the first place.

237
00:13:03,580 --> 00:13:05,680
I've never even tried to,

238
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,480
so I'm still just...

239
00:13:10,050 --> 00:13:15,020
living with one foot stuck
on the most painful day of my life.

240
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,100
What's that supposed to mean?

241
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:24,770
That's even more depressing!

242
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:26,670
Hey.

243
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,310
Fine. Go ahead and cry.

244
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,840
You need something left inside
to cry.

245
00:13:39,950 --> 00:13:41,520
Let me know when you're done crying.

246
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:44,990
I'll brief you on our plan
for tomorrow.

247
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:48,760
A plan for tomorrow?

248
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,430
Why?

249
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:52,530
What are we doing?

250
00:13:52,930 --> 00:13:55,230
Gosh, what is this piece of junk?

251
00:13:55,730 --> 00:13:57,930
Stop calling it a piece of junk.

252
00:13:57,930 --> 00:13:59,770
This thing cost me a pretty penny.

253
00:14:00,570 --> 00:14:03,270
I think this is way worse
than the one we took to Namhae.

254
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:06,140
Come on!
Hey, the GPS works just fine.

255
00:14:06,210 --> 00:14:10,350
Check this out.
The sunroof opens too!

256
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:14,250
Gosh, this is too much.
Close it already.

257
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:16,090
Come on, lighten up.

258
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:18,720
Isn't this a nice change of pace?

259
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:22,760
Did you see? Crypto's up again.

260
00:14:22,830 --> 00:14:26,400
Yes. They updated the network,
and the price has been skyrocketing.

261
00:14:26,430 --> 00:14:28,700
I'm going to sign the lease
for my shop right away.

262
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,800
Hey, did you really do your research
on that shop?

263
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:31,870
I did, okay?

264
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,770
And I really want to quit my job.

265
00:14:34,970 --> 00:14:37,740
I'm so sick of Mr. Song,
and Assistant Manager Oh...

266
00:14:37,810 --> 00:14:40,280
- What about Assistant Manager Oh?
- What?

267
00:14:40,710 --> 00:14:41,940
You know...

268
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:44,050
I've just got a lot on my mind.

269
00:14:46,050 --> 00:14:48,450
So I figured
this was a good chance...

270
00:14:48,450 --> 00:14:50,050
to get it together
and focus on work only.

271
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:52,150
Right, I believe in you, Ji Song.

272
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:54,960
You're a grown-up now, after all.

273
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,860
Come on. Of course.

274
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:59,430
I'm a grown-up, so dinner's on me.

275
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:01,800
So, where are we going anyway?

276
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,830
I told you I'd show you
the real deal...

277
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:06,030
when it came to country food,
didn't I?

278
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:09,740
A thistle rice set
with a view of the countryside.

279
00:15:09,810 --> 00:15:11,770
- You have no idea how good it is.
- Thistle?

280
00:15:11,770 --> 00:15:15,540
I wonder if thistle can really
cure my sorrow.

281
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:20,250
What? What's happening? Eun Sang!

282
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:22,280
- It's raining! Close it!
- Close the sunroof!

283
00:15:22,350 --> 00:15:23,520
- What's wrong? Close it!
- Okay.

284
00:15:24,020 --> 00:15:25,420
What? Why won't it work?

285
00:15:25,490 --> 00:15:27,620
- Hurry!
- Why won't it close?

286
00:15:27,890 --> 00:15:29,690
What? Hey, it's not working!

287
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:31,690
- Gosh!
- Eun Sang!

288
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:32,760
Eun Sang!

289
00:15:34,030 --> 00:15:35,030
Eun Sang!

290
00:15:36,130 --> 00:15:37,670
What is going on with my hair?

291
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:39,470
- Help me see!
- Eun Sang, your hair!

292
00:15:39,470 --> 00:15:40,870
Get my hair off my face!

293
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:44,040
What is all this?

294
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:46,210
I can't see, Ji Song!

295
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:48,040
Where are we even going?

296
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,360
- Eun Sang.
- Eun Sang, get in, quick.

297
00:16:04,430 --> 00:16:06,200
- Goodness.
- How's the car?

298
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:09,970
I guess I can't do long deliveries
in this car.

299
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:11,430
- What do you mean? Deliveries?
- What?

300
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:14,770
The truth is,
I bought this car to earn money.

301
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:17,710
There's the errand center,
green juice delivery, or a taxi.

302
00:16:17,710 --> 00:16:19,510
You can do so much with a car.

303
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:22,410
I can't just sit around idly
after quitting my job.

304
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,310
That figures.

305
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:29,020
You earn all that money
just to make even more money.

306
00:16:29,150 --> 00:16:31,490
Good grief. What a mess.

307
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,490
- What?
- Eun Sang,

308
00:16:35,490 --> 00:16:37,560
a fire truck's coming.

309
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:41,660
- What do I do? Should I back up?
- Yes.

310
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,470
What?

311
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:51,270
Oh, no, why aren't we moving?

312
00:16:52,170 --> 00:16:53,710
- Why aren't we moving?
- It's not working?

313
00:16:53,740 --> 00:16:55,480
- What are we going to do?
- We have a collision up ahead.

314
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:56,750
Please move your vehicle.

315
00:16:56,810 --> 00:16:59,720
Yes, I'm trying to. Just a moment.

316
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:01,320
I'm having some trouble with it.

317
00:17:03,150 --> 00:17:04,450
Hurry up!

318
00:17:05,850 --> 00:17:07,960
Eun Sang!
Hey. Let's get out and push.

319
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,090
- Yes, go push with her.
- Okay, Eun Sang.

320
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:12,360
Just a second!

321
00:17:12,790 --> 00:17:14,600
- We're so sorry!
- Okay.

322
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:16,000
- One, two, three!
- Two, three!

323
00:17:17,330 --> 00:17:18,930
Push! Are you guys pushing?

324
00:17:20,870 --> 00:17:22,470
Are you pushing?

325
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:24,710
Eun Sang, I don't think
this is going to work!

326
00:17:25,070 --> 00:17:27,010
- What do you mean?
- What's wrong with this?

327
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:30,580
What is it?

328
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,220
- Hurry up!
- Did a wheel fall off or something?

329
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:36,290
- We're so sorry!
- One, two, three!

330
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:43,390
Command vehicle en route.
Eight kids in the overturned bus.

331
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:46,400
Eun Sang. I think children were
in an accident.

332
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:49,700
Mom.

333
00:17:49,930 --> 00:17:52,070
A daycare shuttle bus
driving on a rainy road...

334
00:17:52,130 --> 00:17:55,640
has crashed into a guardrail
on a street in Seoul.

335
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,270
Four people were injured
in the crash,

336
00:17:58,340 --> 00:18:01,140
and a five-year-old girl has died.

337
00:18:01,510 --> 00:18:05,250
The child was rushed to the hospital
in cardiac arrest after the crash,

338
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:07,580
but she tragically passed away.

339
00:18:15,690 --> 00:18:17,660
- Just go.
- Excuse me?

340
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:20,030
Just strike my car and go.

341
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,750
What are we going to do, Eun Sang?

342
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:48,860
At 1 p.m. today in Gochon-eup,
Gimpo, Gyeonggi Province,

343
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:51,730
a daycare bus that was
on its way to an event...

344
00:18:51,930 --> 00:18:53,960
tragically overturned.

345
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:56,300
Following the report,
firefighters...

346
00:18:56,300 --> 00:18:59,430
were quickly dispatched to the scene
and began rescue operations.

347
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:01,970
Fortunately, all passengers
were rescued safely...

348
00:19:01,970 --> 00:19:03,940
and taken to a nearby hospital.

349
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:06,880
Onboard the vehicle during the crash
were eight daycare children...

350
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:10,280
- Seems no one was seriously hurt.
- What a relief.

351
00:19:10,510 --> 00:19:11,950
I almost had a heart attack.

352
00:19:12,010 --> 00:19:14,050
The undercarriage is
totally wrecked.

353
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,820
The muffler's badly corroded too.

354
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:18,250
Nothing here is worth salvaging.

355
00:19:18,390 --> 00:19:20,290
If you keep driving it,
it will be trouble on the highway.

356
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:22,160
So it's better to stop now...

357
00:19:22,690 --> 00:19:24,390
than on the highway, right?

358
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:27,030
Let's junk it.

359
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,460
- Okay.
- What?

360
00:19:29,030 --> 00:19:30,330
Are you serious?

361
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:33,770
Wait.
Didn't you spend a fortune on this?

362
00:19:33,770 --> 00:19:34,770
Are you sure about this?

363
00:19:35,170 --> 00:19:36,510
Of course I am.

364
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:40,480
Actually, it's better than okay.

365
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:43,380
Hey, guys.

366
00:19:44,950 --> 00:19:47,420
I'm finally calling it quits.

367
00:19:47,620 --> 00:19:48,850
- What?
- What?

368
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,250
Just like that car,

369
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:53,690
I think it's time for me
to stop too.

370
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:57,360
Just because I made money...

371
00:19:57,430 --> 00:20:00,860
doesn't mean life
will only be full of joy, right?

372
00:20:01,860 --> 00:20:05,170
There will still be times of sadness
and times of anger.

373
00:20:06,970 --> 00:20:10,610
But what's important
is what we choose to focus on...

374
00:20:10,670 --> 00:20:13,210
and the choices we make,
don't you think?

375
00:20:16,510 --> 00:20:18,710
And rather than just keep going,

376
00:20:19,350 --> 00:20:21,450
I'm choosing to stop here.

377
00:20:23,350 --> 00:20:26,660
I want to rest now.
I think I've earned it.

378
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:30,460
What are you two going to do?

379
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:35,530
Ms. Kim Ji Song.

380
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,170
I told you not to take days off,
but I see you did it anyway.

381
00:20:43,410 --> 00:20:44,410
Yes.

382
00:20:44,940 --> 00:20:48,240
The Labor Standards Act guarantees
employees the right to annual leave.

383
00:20:50,510 --> 00:20:53,420
What, "employees?" "Rights?"

384
00:20:53,950 --> 00:20:55,080
Ms. Kim Ji Song,

385
00:20:55,350 --> 00:20:56,520
what do you know?

386
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:58,690
You think you're a legal expert?

387
00:20:58,850 --> 00:21:00,090
You think you know the law?

388
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:02,220
Keep it up.

389
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:05,190
I may not know the law,
but the lawyer I'll hire will.

390
00:21:05,290 --> 00:21:06,360
What?

391
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:12,300
I've avoided you all this time.
Not out of fear, but out of disgust.

392
00:21:12,370 --> 00:21:13,500
But after some thought,

393
00:21:13,570 --> 00:21:16,710
scary or disgusting,
I shouldn't be avoiding it anymore.

394
00:21:17,310 --> 00:21:18,410
If something is disgusting,

395
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:20,680
I should just throw it in the trash.

396
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:24,980
"Trash?"

397
00:21:25,910 --> 00:21:26,920
"Trash?"

398
00:21:28,180 --> 00:21:30,320
Are you calling me trash right now?

399
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:37,890
(Letter of resignation)

400
00:21:39,790 --> 00:21:41,860
Oh, my. That was so cool.

401
00:21:45,370 --> 00:21:46,370
Ms. Kim Ji Song.

402
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:47,900
Are you crazy?

403
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:49,670
Me? Why do you ask?

404
00:21:50,370 --> 00:21:52,640
You power-trip and deny me the leave
I'm entitled to, which is absurd.

405
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,510
You verbally abuse me with nonsense,

406
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:56,380
and you're always
disgustingly touchy.

407
00:21:56,380 --> 00:21:58,650
Aren't you the crazy one, Mr. Song?

408
00:22:00,550 --> 00:22:01,620
Now that I'm quitting,

409
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:04,190
I won't have to call you
Mr. Song anymore.

410
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:06,120
Mister.

411
00:22:09,220 --> 00:22:11,130
"Mister?"

412
00:22:11,290 --> 00:22:14,030
"Mister?"
You've really lost it, haven't you?

413
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:15,360
Mr. Song!

414
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:18,200
- Sir, please don't...
- That hurts! Let me go!

415
00:22:19,370 --> 00:22:20,600
Hey, who do you think you are?

416
00:22:20,740 --> 00:22:22,300
Are you crazy?

417
00:22:22,570 --> 00:22:24,810
I go easy on you people,
and this is what I get. Darn it.

418
00:22:27,580 --> 00:22:30,680
What was that?
Why are you interfering?

419
00:22:30,780 --> 00:22:32,880
Ji Song, are you really quitting?

420
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,750
Was that your resignation letter
you threw at him?

421
00:22:35,380 --> 00:22:37,750
You defended me without knowing?

422
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:41,720
I'm fine since I'm quitting,
but what about you, Mr. Oh?

423
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:42,920
Don't worry about me.

424
00:22:43,490 --> 00:22:45,590
And you deserved to be defended.

425
00:22:45,730 --> 00:22:47,530
Why shouldn't you get your days off?

426
00:22:47,530 --> 00:22:50,830
Plus, at the end of last month,
you pulled all-nighters by yourself.

427
00:22:51,300 --> 00:22:54,400
And you were also the one who fixed
the accounting mistake yourself.

428
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:59,140
I really hate the thought
of you quitting.

429
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:03,280
But still, Ji Song,

430
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:07,250
you have every right
to do whatever you want.

431
00:23:07,250 --> 00:23:08,350
Look down.

432
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:12,220
What? Okay.

433
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:17,630
I'm about to start a business
relying only on my gut feeling.

434
00:23:18,290 --> 00:23:20,900
So what am I supposed to do
if my gut keeps being so wrong?

435
00:23:23,130 --> 00:23:24,830
What do you mean,
your gut was wrong?

436
00:23:27,970 --> 00:23:29,600
I didn't think I'd get butterflies!

437
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,240
Never did I think...

438
00:23:32,870 --> 00:23:35,080
I'd get butterflies for you, Mr. Oh.

439
00:23:36,610 --> 00:23:39,850
But you keep making my heart race,
and acting like this...

440
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:43,420
What am I supposed to do?

441
00:23:49,620 --> 00:23:50,730
(Jung Da Hee)

442
00:23:54,060 --> 00:23:57,630
It's a shame
I have to leave so suddenly.

443
00:23:58,030 --> 00:23:59,700
You're just giving us the creeps.

444
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,670
There was a bit
of an unfortunate incident,

445
00:24:02,970 --> 00:24:05,910
and I regret leaving without
clearing up the misunderstanding.

446
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:10,310
But being able to work
with all of you...

447
00:24:10,910 --> 00:24:12,110
was a true pleasure.

448
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:17,750
Well then, I'll be taking my leave.

449
00:24:34,570 --> 00:24:35,770
Well, this is awkward.

450
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,110
I thought I gave...

451
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:41,740
a pretty moving speech back then.

452
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:44,080
It's amazing
how little you've changed.

453
00:24:45,710 --> 00:24:46,980
I wonder...

454
00:24:47,180 --> 00:24:50,190
- what you were expecting.
- Gosh.

455
00:24:56,790 --> 00:24:58,060
Here, just take this.

456
00:24:59,690 --> 00:25:01,130
About the snack subscription box...

457
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:04,000
You're aware there's still room
for improvement, right?

458
00:25:05,370 --> 00:25:07,100
You're going to have to work
a lot harder.

459
00:25:13,410 --> 00:25:14,410
Darn it.

460
00:25:21,250 --> 00:25:24,550
I've compiled the handover materials
into this file for you.

461
00:25:24,820 --> 00:25:27,120
It has everything from A to Z,

462
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:29,460
so just check here
if you get confused.

463
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:31,160
Okay, thank you.

464
00:25:31,890 --> 00:25:33,190
(3rd floor meeting room,
12th floor hallway)

465
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,300
If you time it right, you can get
about ten minutes alone.

466
00:25:37,670 --> 00:25:40,700
No, wait. You can rest
for about 20 minutes there.

467
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,100
When you're working hard
and feel worn out,

468
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:45,540
you should go to one of these places
and take a break.

469
00:25:45,970 --> 00:25:48,810
I never rested when I was tired,

470
00:25:48,810 --> 00:25:50,780
and I never cried when I was sad,

471
00:25:51,610 --> 00:25:54,780
so it felt like
something inside me just broke.

472
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:58,190
Don't you be like that, Ji Hye.
All right?

473
00:25:58,420 --> 00:26:01,790
Take time to cry and rest.
Pace yourself.

474
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:03,290
That's how you last in the long run.

475
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:05,360
Okay.

476
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:07,560
Eun Sang.

477
00:26:12,130 --> 00:26:14,000
Come on, why are you all crying...

478
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,570
like it's the end of the world?

479
00:26:17,470 --> 00:26:19,310
Come on, everyone. Chin up.

480
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,810
- Have grit! You must...
- Eun Sang...

481
00:26:24,210 --> 00:26:26,280
Don't just live by being tough
all the time.

482
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:28,920
If you ever feel like
having a stiff drink,

483
00:26:29,350 --> 00:26:31,590
call me anytime. Got it?

484
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:34,720
No, really. Please do call.

485
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:36,930
Eun Sang.

486
00:26:39,530 --> 00:26:40,530
Okay.

487
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:44,830
- What?
- About this promotion,

488
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:47,600
they backed HR's Team Leader Choi.

489
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:50,210
No, but they promised I was next.

490
00:26:50,210 --> 00:26:52,770
Mr. Choi has a widowed mother.

491
00:26:52,770 --> 00:26:54,210
He's also got four kids.

492
00:26:54,610 --> 00:26:56,950
And he also went to the same school
as Director Kim.

493
00:26:59,310 --> 00:27:00,620
As for you, Mr. Ko,

494
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:04,590
let's aim for the next one.
All right?

495
00:27:11,460 --> 00:27:14,060
This is driving me crazy.

496
00:27:14,660 --> 00:27:16,160
What am I going to tell her?

497
00:27:20,130 --> 00:27:22,200
(Honey, I'm just joking,)

498
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:24,540
(but what if I quit my job
and opened a cafe?)

499
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:31,180
Should I get into crypto
or something?

500
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:35,850
Oh, gosh.

501
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,650
I'm so baffled and speechless!

502
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:40,920
What kind of psycho brat
throws a resignation letter...

503
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,190
in her superior's face?

504
00:27:42,290 --> 00:27:45,190
And when did I ever even touch her?

505
00:27:45,260 --> 00:27:47,760
If her superior treats her nicely,

506
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,330
she should know how to be grateful.

507
00:27:49,330 --> 00:27:50,900
How dare she be arrogant
for someone in her position!

508
00:27:51,170 --> 00:27:52,870
Just because
she made some money off crypto,

509
00:27:52,870 --> 00:27:54,340
she thinks she's hot stuff.

510
00:27:54,770 --> 00:27:57,410
Kids these days.
They have no darn manners.

511
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:01,710
But what's with you,
just sitting there like that?

512
00:28:03,910 --> 00:28:05,750
Now that Eun Sang is gone,

513
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:09,480
my future looks bleak and scary.

514
00:28:13,020 --> 00:28:15,660
But you didn't actually
touch her, did you?

515
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:18,460
I barely grazed her.

516
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:19,460
Hey!

517
00:28:19,930 --> 00:28:22,960
- Goodness!
- You are a real jerk, aren't you?

518
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,730
- Are you talking to me?
- Yes.

519
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:27,200
I couldn't stand
hearing about crypto...

520
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:28,370
and about
pursuing self-actualization...

521
00:28:28,370 --> 00:28:30,770
while they messed around at work.

522
00:28:30,770 --> 00:28:31,810
But you're a jerk.

523
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:32,970
