can you imagine how they feel?

526
00:28:38,350 --> 00:28:41,180
- No wonder they want to leave.
- Hey!

527
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:42,250
What? You got a problem?

528
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:44,820
Why should I understand
their feelings...

529
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:46,650
because of a jerk like you?

530
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:51,030
Why can't I be the grumpy old boss
in peace because of you?

531
00:28:51,090 --> 00:28:52,090
Darn it!

532
00:28:52,390 --> 00:28:53,530
Why you little...

533
00:28:55,030 --> 00:28:57,700
Hey, Ko Dae Young.
Hey, where are you...

534
00:28:58,200 --> 00:29:01,270
Hey, what's his problem?

535
00:29:01,270 --> 00:29:04,310
- Does he not want to work here?
- I guess so?

536
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,410
- Unbelievable.
- I wonder why.

537
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:09,680
I like working here, though.

538
00:29:11,910 --> 00:29:13,850
Only if it weren't for
old-school guys like you.

539
00:29:16,450 --> 00:29:17,450
Hey!

540
00:29:18,220 --> 00:29:19,290
Hey!

541
00:29:26,190 --> 00:29:28,900
Do I really have to be here
this late on the day I quit?

542
00:29:29,260 --> 00:29:30,570
I'm so sick of this.

543
00:29:31,300 --> 00:29:33,470
What can we do? We had to work late.

544
00:29:34,540 --> 00:29:35,600
All right!

545
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,670
Let's all say a few words
before the big moment.

546
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:42,140
Well, about that...

547
00:29:42,740 --> 00:29:43,980
Can a few words even cover it?

548
00:29:45,150 --> 00:29:46,910
We have it too!

549
00:29:46,980 --> 00:29:48,520
Something to turn this all around.

550
00:29:49,420 --> 00:29:50,750
Our ace in the hole!

551
00:29:51,090 --> 00:29:52,550
I can't bear to watch...

552
00:29:53,090 --> 00:29:54,260
you two collapse.

553
00:29:54,260 --> 00:29:55,760
I won't let that happen to you two!

554
00:29:55,820 --> 00:29:57,430
- Oh, my.
- Let's go! To the moon!

555
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:59,660
- To the moon!
- Let's go! To the moon!

556
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:01,460
Get ready. Let's do this.

557
00:30:03,460 --> 00:30:04,830
(Your buy order has been
successfully placed.)

558
00:30:06,670 --> 00:30:10,770
I'm going to be with you guys
until the very end.

559
00:30:11,210 --> 00:30:13,540
Then let's go all the way.

560
00:30:13,740 --> 00:30:16,080
- Let's keep going!
- Let's keep going!

561
00:30:16,810 --> 00:30:19,510
But if I had to leave
one last thought,

562
00:30:19,950 --> 00:30:20,950
I...

563
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:23,050
I'm free!

564
00:30:24,090 --> 00:30:25,220
Let's do it.

565
00:30:25,220 --> 00:30:26,920
(Enderion, Confirm Sell?)

566
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:27,990
(Your sell order has been
successfully placed.)

567
00:30:30,860 --> 00:30:33,760
Good job, Jung Da Hae.

568
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:39,130
(Enderion, Confirm Sell?)

569
00:30:39,130 --> 00:30:40,130
(Your sell order has been
successfully placed.)

570
00:30:42,170 --> 00:30:44,010
Kang Eun Sang,
you've worked hard too!

571
00:30:48,010 --> 00:30:49,710
(Enderion, Confirm Sell?)

572
00:30:49,780 --> 00:30:50,780
(Your sell order has been
successfully placed.)

573
00:30:52,150 --> 00:30:54,380
Kim Ji Song, you did great too!

574
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:00,890
And at this very moment...

575
00:31:01,420 --> 00:31:02,460
Ta-da!

576
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:06,060
- Student loans paid off!
- Gosh, no more debt!

577
00:31:06,230 --> 00:31:07,260
Congratulations!

578
00:31:07,830 --> 00:31:11,300
No, we're the ones
who should be thanking you.

579
00:31:11,630 --> 00:31:12,700
We owe it all to you.

580
00:31:13,100 --> 00:31:14,100
What?

581
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:16,800
For giving me a life...

582
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:19,710
I never could have imagined
or even dared to dream of.

583
00:31:20,270 --> 00:31:23,780
And for
pulling me into this grand story.

584
00:31:24,610 --> 00:31:25,810
Thank you for everything, Eun Sang.

585
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:29,880
Me too.

586
00:31:31,650 --> 00:31:35,390
I'm incredibly grateful, Eun Sang!
No, scratch that. I love you.

587
00:31:35,790 --> 00:31:38,060
Me too! I love you, Kang Eun Sang!

588
00:31:38,130 --> 00:31:40,330
You guys. This is so cheesy. Stop.

589
00:31:40,390 --> 00:31:42,260
Hey. Get off me.

590
00:31:45,270 --> 00:31:46,270
Goodness.

591
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:49,670
- What's that?
- Looks like there's a festival.

592
00:31:49,900 --> 00:31:51,840
There's that university
nearby, right?

593
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:54,310
It's perfect.

594
00:31:55,980 --> 00:31:57,380
It's absolutely beautiful.

595
00:31:58,110 --> 00:31:59,110
Everyone!

596
00:31:59,410 --> 00:32:01,480
It's a beautiful night!

597
00:32:38,820 --> 00:32:40,120
Right, I quit my job.

598
00:32:43,690 --> 00:32:44,830
I can sleep in.

599
00:33:38,050 --> 00:33:39,350
In the void,

600
00:33:39,350 --> 00:33:41,720
where the numbers and goals
that once filled her life...

601
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:43,150
used to be,

602
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,860
a moment of mourning
found its way in.

603
00:34:07,510 --> 00:34:11,710
It was like she was finally learning
how to truly cry.

604
00:34:12,350 --> 00:34:13,650
She cried endlessly.

605
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:15,920
She cried her heart out.

606
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:37,840
Da Hae!

607
00:34:38,470 --> 00:34:39,470
Da Hae?

608
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:41,380
Hey.

609
00:34:41,740 --> 00:34:42,810
Where's Eun Sang?

610
00:34:43,410 --> 00:34:44,450
She left.

611
00:34:44,650 --> 00:34:45,650
What?

612
00:34:46,110 --> 00:34:47,110
(I'll be back after I cry.)

613
00:34:47,110 --> 00:34:49,180
Just how much
does she plan on crying?

614
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:52,420
So, you have no idea where she went?

615
00:34:52,850 --> 00:34:53,850
No.

616
00:34:55,220 --> 00:34:56,220
But...

617
00:34:57,430 --> 00:34:58,790
let's just give her some space.

618
00:34:59,390 --> 00:35:00,560
Let her cry her heart out.

619
00:35:03,860 --> 00:35:06,100
What about you?
What happened with that deposit?

620
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,340
You can't get it back?

621
00:35:08,170 --> 00:35:09,170
Well...

622
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:11,610
I'll just have to chalk it up
as an expensive life lesson.

623
00:35:12,610 --> 00:35:14,180
Ji Song had been scammed.

624
00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:18,880
The place Ji Song put a deposit on
was a fraudulent listing.

625
00:35:20,510 --> 00:35:22,280
Even though it must have been
a devastating blow,

626
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:24,420
- I can't believe she just left.
- Ji Song no longer lets...

627
00:35:24,420 --> 00:35:27,790
one setback keep her down for long.

628
00:35:28,490 --> 00:35:29,490
Look at this.

629
00:35:31,860 --> 00:35:33,260
Are you really okay?

630
00:35:34,060 --> 00:35:35,230
I have to just shake it off.

631
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:37,600
Plus, I've already got my eye
on a new place.

632
00:35:39,230 --> 00:35:42,770
Gosh, our Ji Song is
all grown up now.

633
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:44,540
Are you going right now?

634
00:35:45,070 --> 00:35:46,110
What are you going to do there?

635
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:50,910
And then there was me.

636
00:36:05,290 --> 00:36:06,530
This is always a good sight.

637
00:36:08,100 --> 00:36:10,560
Well, it would've been nicer
with him.

638
00:36:19,740 --> 00:36:20,740
Will you...

639
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:22,880
marry me?

640
00:36:32,450 --> 00:36:33,490
I miss you.

641
00:36:37,930 --> 00:36:38,930
I miss you.

642
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:58,180
July 20, 1969.

643
00:36:58,650 --> 00:37:02,780
The historic moment when Apollo 11
made the 1st manned moon landing.

644
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:07,920
But maybe the real story
is what happened after the landing.

645
00:37:08,020 --> 00:37:10,790
(1 year later)

646
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:14,060
After all, just getting to the moon
wasn't the end of the journey.

647
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,730
What path you should take next,

648
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:19,000
and what direction
you're currently facing.

649
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,030
That's what's more important.

650
00:37:20,430 --> 00:37:23,670
But that's something that's hard
to figure out on your own.

651
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:26,970
After all, Apollo 11 was in
constant communication with Earth,

652
00:37:27,040 --> 00:37:29,010
which was how it was able to
land safely on the moon,

653
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:32,080
and how the world could see
that moment as it happened.

654
00:37:32,410 --> 00:37:36,250
Isn't communication about learning
where you're both headed...

655
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:39,990
and gradually aligning your paths
so you can walk forward together?

656
00:37:40,860 --> 00:37:43,590
Here are some more examples...

657
00:37:43,590 --> 00:37:44,930
of why workplace
communication matters.

