661
00:38:06,810 --> 00:38:07,820
(Kang Eun Sang:
Customers in, sales out)

662
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:10,150
(Jung Da Hae: I guarantee
this place is good.)

663
00:38:13,820 --> 00:38:17,190
Ms. Kim,
your mango tanghulu is ready.

664
00:38:17,260 --> 00:38:18,360
Thank you.

665
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:23,830
Seriously, boss, how did you know
the shop would do so well?

666
00:38:24,030 --> 00:38:25,070
You just have good instincts?

667
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:27,700
I've had my moments.

668
00:38:28,670 --> 00:38:33,370
Back then, trusting my instincts
was all I really had going for me.

669
00:38:33,570 --> 00:38:35,340
I guess that's why
I was so obsessed with it.

670
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:39,250
I guess you could say it felt like
my greatest weapon back then.

671
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:43,280
- And not anymore?
- Gosh, of course not.

672
00:38:43,720 --> 00:38:45,650
Now, I'm my own greatest weapon.

673
00:38:47,190 --> 00:38:48,190
Just you wait.

674
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:51,360
Tanghulu will be even bigger soon.

675
00:38:51,490 --> 00:38:52,530
And you know why?

676
00:38:52,590 --> 00:38:54,030
Because I'm going to make it happen.

677
00:38:54,900 --> 00:38:56,260
I sure hope so.

678
00:38:56,660 --> 00:39:00,770
The landlord here is giving you
a great deal on the rent.

679
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:05,710
- This is how you'll get rich.
- Stop.

680
00:39:05,940 --> 00:39:06,940
I appreciate it.

681
00:39:07,610 --> 00:39:08,610
Mom, here.

682
00:39:09,010 --> 00:39:11,310
I got you something for the season.

683
00:39:11,310 --> 00:39:12,510
This color looks great on you.

684
00:39:12,810 --> 00:39:14,320
You shouldn't have.

685
00:39:14,550 --> 00:39:16,320
Thank you. I'll wear it often.

686
00:39:16,620 --> 00:39:20,220
Right. And also,
Ji Song packed these just for you.

687
00:39:20,450 --> 00:39:21,960
It's strawberry and grape tanghulu.

688
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:24,660
But she runs a business.
Is it okay to give freebies?

689
00:39:24,660 --> 00:39:26,530
Thank her for me. I'll enjoy them.

690
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:30,560
Right. And this is for you, Dad.

691
00:39:31,470 --> 00:39:32,630
For me? What is it?

692
00:39:34,900 --> 00:39:36,640
I look good in any color,

693
00:39:36,900 --> 00:39:39,170
and I like tomato just as much
as strawberry or grape.

694
00:39:40,540 --> 00:39:41,640
It's your phone bill.

695
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:44,450
I see.

696
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:47,620
Of course. I should pay it.

697
00:39:50,820 --> 00:39:52,720
Excuse me for a second.

698
00:40:03,460 --> 00:40:05,130
Don't be so hard on him.

699
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,970
Like it or not, we live together.

700
00:40:07,970 --> 00:40:09,270
When he's hunched over and moping,

701
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:11,140
do you have any idea
how much that gets on my nerves?

702
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:12,440
What did I do?

703
00:40:13,470 --> 00:40:16,280
Still, it's not like
your father is a complete failure.

704
00:40:17,780 --> 00:40:19,350
Name one thing he's done right.

705
00:40:20,450 --> 00:40:21,780
For one thing, your father...

706
00:40:24,220 --> 00:40:25,620
He has never done drugs.

707
00:40:26,120 --> 00:40:27,250
And he's never murdered anyone.

708
00:40:28,090 --> 00:40:30,260
Gosh, just stop.

709
00:40:31,230 --> 00:40:32,630
Lately,

710
00:40:33,130 --> 00:40:35,160
it looks like
he's been studying stocks.

711
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:37,630
Another one of his useless schemes.

712
00:40:38,230 --> 00:40:40,970
Tell him to get a real job
if he wants to support himself.

713
00:40:41,070 --> 00:40:42,870
And you? Is making a living
the only reason you work?

714
00:40:45,370 --> 00:40:46,570
Mom, whose side are you on?

715
00:40:46,570 --> 00:40:47,980
I'm not taking sides.

716
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:51,080
We're all
in the same miserable boat.

717
00:41:00,150 --> 00:41:01,220
See you.

718
00:41:02,490 --> 00:41:03,490
What?

719
00:41:03,890 --> 00:41:04,890
Are you leaving already?

720
00:41:05,860 --> 00:41:07,390
Look, I bought ice cream.

721
00:41:07,700 --> 00:41:09,300
- What am I, a kid?
- Goodness.

722
00:41:10,230 --> 00:41:13,000
Come on, I even got yours in a cone.

723
00:41:13,100 --> 00:41:15,500
Gosh, you're unbelievable.

724
00:41:16,340 --> 00:41:18,410
He doesn't commit murder.
He doesn't do drugs.

725
00:41:18,940 --> 00:41:21,110
And he buys his daughter's ice cream
in a cone.

726
00:41:21,540 --> 00:41:22,640
What are you talking about?

727
00:41:23,140 --> 00:41:25,780
You make it impossible
not to be a good daughter.

728
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:33,520
What's this?

729
00:41:34,820 --> 00:41:35,820
Investment money.

730
00:41:36,460 --> 00:41:37,490
What?

731
00:41:38,430 --> 00:41:39,990
Didn't you say there was something
you wanted to do?

732
00:41:42,660 --> 00:41:44,060
From what I can tell,

733
00:41:44,630 --> 00:41:48,140
you're just not the type of person
to ever find a four-leaf clover.

734
00:41:48,500 --> 00:41:50,200
You were born with terrible luck.

735
00:41:52,010 --> 00:41:56,410
Yet, you have all these ambitions,
wanting to do this and that.

736
00:41:58,380 --> 00:42:00,110
But who can blame you for that?

737
00:42:00,710 --> 00:42:01,980
I was the same way.

738
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:09,590
So, just this once,
trust me and take a leap of faith.

739
00:42:11,390 --> 00:42:13,130
Just this one time,

740
00:42:14,700 --> 00:42:16,530
I'll be your good luck.

741
00:42:18,970 --> 00:42:20,070
Da Hae.

742
00:42:21,570 --> 00:42:25,340
But don't get in over your head.
Only go as far as you can manage.

743
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:26,610
Please.

744
00:42:27,040 --> 00:42:29,880
Hey, this time's different.
I really did my homework.

745
00:42:30,410 --> 00:42:34,210
I looked through the reports
and followed the earnings.

746
00:42:34,750 --> 00:42:37,620
I even watched the CEO interviews.

747
00:42:38,250 --> 00:42:39,550
What's the company's name?

748
00:42:40,020 --> 00:42:41,460
You know.

749
00:42:41,820 --> 00:42:45,260
Mask? Is it Elon Musk?

750
00:42:45,260 --> 00:42:47,360
The one that guy runs.

751
00:42:48,530 --> 00:42:53,200
Mark my words,
the age of electric cars is coming.

752
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:55,240
I'm telling you, this is the one.

753
00:42:55,670 --> 00:42:58,340
Please. Like I'd believe you.

754
00:42:58,470 --> 00:43:00,970
You can laugh all you want,
but this is the real deal.

755
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:03,110
You always say, "This is it."

756
00:43:03,110 --> 00:43:06,180
No, I thought it was real back then,
but I really studied this one.

757
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:07,980
- This one...
- You said you studied then too.

758
00:43:08,050 --> 00:43:10,020
Look, when it rains,
the ground gets wet.

759
00:43:10,020 --> 00:43:11,120
- So?
- It's just like that.

760
00:43:11,120 --> 00:43:13,650
- It's a sure thing.
- This is hopeless. Give it back!

761
00:43:13,720 --> 00:43:14,720
- Come on.
- I'm serious.

762
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:20,130
That was a request from Lee Ju Ah
from Gwanak-gu.

763
00:43:20,190 --> 00:43:22,230
We just enjoyed the song
by Ham Ji Woo.

764
00:43:23,030 --> 00:43:25,100
Now, some of you
might already know this,

765
00:43:25,170 --> 00:43:28,340
but he's an artist active
in the English-speaking world.

766
00:43:29,070 --> 00:43:31,710
He's been getting quite popular
here in Korea lately too.

