00:43:36,940 --> 00:43:40,850
"I don't want to make music
to comfort people."

770
00:43:41,580 --> 00:43:44,590
"I just hope people's lives
aren't so difficult..."

771
00:43:44,590 --> 00:43:47,490
"or lonely that they'd need
to be comforted."

772
00:43:48,160 --> 00:43:50,520
"For people's best,
happiest moments,"

773
00:43:50,590 --> 00:43:53,160
"I just want to make music
that's like a celebration."

774
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:56,760
"You think my songs are too mellow?"

775
00:43:57,260 --> 00:44:00,070
"You don't think I won't make much
in royalties?"

776
00:44:00,070 --> 00:44:01,370
"Don't worry about it."

777
00:44:01,370 --> 00:44:04,870
"When I had a corporate job,
I saved up plenty of bonus money,"

778
00:44:04,870 --> 00:44:06,070
"so it's okay."

779
00:44:06,610 --> 00:44:08,980
"So, everyone, be happy."

780
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:12,210
"Make sure to be happy."

781
00:44:12,810 --> 00:44:14,350
He's a fun guy, isn't he?

782
00:44:14,750 --> 00:44:17,320
I hear he'll have
a show in Korea soon.

783
00:44:17,890 --> 00:44:19,320
I should probably go check it out.

784
00:44:22,590 --> 00:44:23,590
(Jung Da Hee)

785
00:44:23,720 --> 00:44:25,830
Looks like your ex has a concert
coming up.

786
00:44:28,630 --> 00:44:29,630
(Mobile ticket)

787
00:44:32,800 --> 00:44:35,100
(Ham Ji Woo, "With You")

788
00:44:36,270 --> 00:44:37,970
My ex?

789
00:44:39,140 --> 00:44:40,570
I said, tuna.

790
00:44:41,140 --> 00:44:43,410
Sashimi? Yes, tuna.

791
00:44:43,810 --> 00:44:47,050
So, in our dressing room,
you must have it set up.

792
00:44:47,110 --> 00:44:48,950
That's a requirement to book us.

793
00:44:49,150 --> 00:44:51,120
Yes, but sorry about this time.

794
00:44:51,180 --> 00:44:53,420
Right now, we are already in Korea.

795
00:44:54,520 --> 00:44:56,990
Next time you invite us again,

796
00:44:57,490 --> 00:44:59,190
we would be very thankful.

797
00:44:59,890 --> 00:45:03,500
So, for the detailed schedule,
we can touch base nearer the date.

798
00:45:03,500 --> 00:45:05,500
And the performance fee...

799
00:45:07,170 --> 00:45:08,940
Please make sure the event fee is...

800
00:45:08,940 --> 00:45:10,870
clearly stated
in the contract in advance.

801
00:45:10,870 --> 00:45:13,510
I would appreciate it
if the payment could be completed...

802
00:45:13,510 --> 00:45:15,010
within one week of the performance.

803
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:17,310
Any additional documents
will be sent through the label.

804
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:18,750
Okay, bye.

805
00:45:23,120 --> 00:45:24,820
How are you suddenly so fluent...

806
00:45:24,820 --> 00:45:26,190
when talking about
the performance fee?

807
00:45:26,250 --> 00:45:27,250
Shut it.

808
00:45:27,320 --> 00:45:29,790
Seriously, for a 200-seat theater,

809
00:45:29,860 --> 00:45:32,490
you think it's wise to give up a gig
in Manchester?

810
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:35,500
Why does the venue's size matter?
It's the meaning that counts.

811
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:37,500
No, I mean, the "meaning..."

812
00:45:38,630 --> 00:45:40,370
Let me explain this to you again.

813
00:45:40,500 --> 00:45:42,400
If you two haven't talked in a year,

814
00:45:42,500 --> 00:45:43,570
that means you broke up.

815
00:45:43,570 --> 00:45:46,370
We, as a society,
have agreed to call that a breakup.

816
00:45:46,440 --> 00:45:47,770
Oh, come on.

817
00:45:48,380 --> 00:45:50,710
I just came to Korea
to perform for a good cause.

818
00:45:50,780 --> 00:45:51,910
I'll get fans here...

819
00:45:51,910 --> 00:45:54,410
and donate the profit.
Isn't that great?

820
00:45:54,510 --> 00:45:56,080
You look like you need donations.

821
00:45:56,080 --> 00:45:58,320
How can you wear flip-flops
all year?

822
00:45:58,390 --> 00:46:00,220
I'm telling you, my feet hurt.

823
00:46:00,220 --> 00:46:01,690
I can't wear dress shoes.

824
00:46:02,720 --> 00:46:04,560
Right. I'm sure they hurt.

825
00:46:05,330 --> 00:46:08,200
You're probably still hurting. Yes.

826
00:46:10,130 --> 00:46:12,100
Please, just leave it.
I can do it myself.

827
00:46:12,170 --> 00:46:15,870
Oh, no, it's okay.
This is too heavy for you, Ji Song.

828
00:46:16,040 --> 00:46:17,140
I can handle it.

829
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:20,470
You must be so busy with work,
but you always help me like this.

830
00:46:20,810 --> 00:46:23,540
It's good exercise.

831
00:46:24,010 --> 00:46:25,080
And I kind of enjoy it.

832
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:28,680
Sorry, we're closed...

833
00:46:31,220 --> 00:46:32,220
Ji Song.

834
00:46:32,950 --> 00:46:33,950
Wei Lin?

835
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,560
What are you doing here?

836
00:46:44,030 --> 00:46:47,330
I came to see you, Ji Song,
and to check out your shop.

837
00:46:47,500 --> 00:46:48,540
Kind of like
killing 2 birds with 1 stone.

838
00:46:48,800 --> 00:46:50,400
"Killing 2 birds with 1 stone?"

839
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:52,870
Where did you learn
a phrase like that?

840
00:46:53,170 --> 00:46:57,040
You're the one who said
my Korean wasn't very good.

841
00:46:57,610 --> 00:46:58,880
So I've been studying.

842
00:46:59,950 --> 00:47:01,150
Good for you.

843
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:04,220
A good-looking foreigner like you
who also speaks Korean well?

844
00:47:04,380 --> 00:47:05,990
That's a killer combination.

845
00:47:05,990 --> 00:47:07,090
So cute.

846
00:47:08,190 --> 00:47:11,590
If you have some free time,
could you be my tour guide?

847
00:47:11,660 --> 00:47:14,860
- I've been wanting to see Namsan.
- A tour guide?

848
00:47:15,860 --> 00:47:18,800
Of course. From Namsan
to K-barbecue pork belly,

849
00:47:18,870 --> 00:47:20,670
I'll give you a full-course tour.

850
00:47:20,670 --> 00:47:22,440
I like pork belly too.

851
00:47:23,600 --> 00:47:25,770
Mr. Oh, did you say something?

852
00:47:26,340 --> 00:47:28,710
What? Nothing.

853
00:47:28,910 --> 00:47:31,510
The trash. I said
I'm going to take out the trash.

854
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:35,480
No, it's...
I said we'd do it together later.

855
00:47:35,550 --> 00:47:36,750
- Oh, no, it's fine.
- Ji Song.

856
00:47:38,620 --> 00:47:41,620
If you're ever having a hard time,
you have to call me.

857
00:47:41,820 --> 00:47:43,390
We're close enough for that.

858
00:47:43,720 --> 00:47:45,060
We're friends, after all.

859
00:47:47,590 --> 00:47:48,660
Okay.

860
00:47:57,370 --> 00:47:58,570
Mr. Oh!

861
00:47:59,670 --> 00:48:00,870
I said we should do it together.

862
00:48:00,970 --> 00:48:02,880
No, I'm fine. Why did you come out?

863
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:04,950
- Let me...
- Oh, no, it's okay.

864
00:48:05,810 --> 00:48:07,010
Still,

865
00:48:07,410 --> 00:48:08,720
thank you.

866
00:48:11,520 --> 00:48:13,590
Isn't Wei Lin waiting for you?

867
00:48:14,520 --> 00:48:15,860
He left.

868
00:48:16,690 --> 00:48:17,890
He left?

869
00:48:19,830 --> 00:48:23,000
Couldn't he stay a bit longer?
Why was he in such a rush?

870
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:27,330
He has his own life.
I guess he had other plans.

871
00:48:28,070 --> 00:48:30,440
What plans could be more important
than seeing you, Ji Song?

872
00:48:30,900 --> 00:48:33,040
And what's this about him
having his own life?

873
00:48:33,910 --> 00:48:34,940
Excuse me?

874
00:48:42,350 --> 00:48:44,450
Ji Song.
I'm no longer an assistant manager.

875
00:48:44,450 --> 00:48:45,490
I'm a team leader now.

876
00:48:45,820 --> 00:48:47,390
Mr. Song resigned recently,

877
00:48:47,490 --> 00:48:49,190
so I got promoted.
I'm Team Leader Oh now.

878
00:48:49,190 --> 00:48:51,860
Really?
Why are you only telling me now?

879
00:48:51,930 --> 00:48:53,060
Remember a while ago...

880
00:48:53,060 --> 00:48:55,160
when I couldn't come
to the shop for three days?

881
00:48:55,230 --> 00:48:57,600
I was getting a gallstone removed.

882
00:48:57,600 --> 00:48:59,400
I had a big polyp right here.

883
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:01,970
What? Why didn't you tell me?
Are you okay now?

884
00:49:02,070 --> 00:49:03,400
- And there's more.
- More?

885
00:49:03,540 --> 00:49:04,770
What else is there?

886
00:49:04,840 --> 00:49:06,040
Of course.

887
00:49:06,440 --> 00:49:09,180
I have a life of my own too.

888
00:49:09,840 --> 00:49:12,280
It's just not that important.

889
00:49:13,980 --> 00:49:16,080
I know this is going
to sound ridiculous,

890
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:18,650
but no matter how much
I think about it,

891
00:49:19,350 --> 00:49:20,990
for me,

892
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:22,890
nothing is more important than you.

893
00:49:24,960 --> 00:49:26,560
I don't even need a private life.

894
00:49:28,830 --> 00:49:30,330
In my life,

895
00:49:31,700 --> 00:49:33,330
there's nothing I want...

896
00:49:34,300 --> 00:49:36,100
to be as devoted to as you.

897
00:49:37,270 --> 00:49:39,570
That's why I...

898
00:49:47,210 --> 00:49:48,450
Darn it.

899
00:49:48,850 --> 00:49:50,750
What is it? What's wrong?

900
00:49:50,880 --> 00:49:52,420
- What?
- I just feel so...

901
00:49:52,990 --> 00:49:56,390
- so pathetic.
- What?

902
00:49:56,390 --> 00:50:01,160
I know very well that I can't
compare to a great guy like Wei Lin.

903
00:50:01,160 --> 00:50:03,200
Yet, here I am
making this lame confession...

904
00:50:03,260 --> 00:50:05,630
- to try to win your heart.
- A confession?

905
00:50:07,100 --> 00:50:09,900
Wait, if we're already dating,
why would we need a confession?

906
00:50:11,300 --> 00:50:12,670
- What?
- What?

907
00:50:12,740 --> 00:50:14,170
- What?
- What?

908
00:50:14,710 --> 00:50:17,140
Wait. We're date...

909
00:50:17,210 --> 00:50:18,380
We're dating...

910
00:50:18,710 --> 00:50:20,110
Are we dating?

911
00:50:21,750 --> 00:50:23,920
You mean we haven't been?

912
00:50:24,250 --> 00:50:25,690
- What?
- What?

913
00:50:29,420 --> 00:50:33,530
Then why do you think I said that
a year ago?

914
00:50:35,900 --> 00:50:36,960
Never did I think...

915
00:50:37,800 --> 00:50:40,500
I'd get butterflies for you, Mr. Oh.

916
00:50:41,570 --> 00:50:42,570
Well...

917
00:50:42,840 --> 00:50:43,840
So that...

918
00:50:45,110 --> 00:50:46,470
So that meant...

919
00:50:47,540 --> 00:50:50,010
- Mr. Oh!
- Gosh. Yes?

920
00:50:50,010 --> 00:50:51,810
What were we this whole time?

921
00:50:51,910 --> 00:50:52,910
Then,

922
00:50:52,980 --> 00:50:54,410
what were you doing all this time?

923
00:50:54,610 --> 00:50:55,780
If we weren't even dating,

924
00:50:55,850 --> 00:50:57,050
why were you helping at the shop?

925
00:50:57,050 --> 00:50:58,320
Why'd you walk me home every day?

926
00:50:58,520 --> 00:50:59,990
That's because...

927
00:51:00,250 --> 00:51:01,250
That's because...

928
00:51:01,620 --> 00:51:04,860
No, but even so,
that doesn't mean we were dating...

929
00:51:05,130 --> 00:51:06,530
That's not what dating is, is it?

930
00:51:06,860 --> 00:51:09,100
I've never even held your hand.

931
00:51:09,360 --> 00:51:12,570
That's because
I figured that was just you.

932
00:51:12,630 --> 00:51:15,070
I figured you were
taking things slow.

933
00:51:17,740 --> 00:51:18,940
Then hold my hand now.

934
00:51:22,410 --> 00:51:23,480
Wait.

935
00:51:25,180 --> 00:51:26,980
I've never even hugged you.

936
00:51:29,350 --> 00:51:30,720
Then hug me now.

937
00:51:33,690 --> 00:51:34,720
And...

938
00:51:36,520 --> 00:51:37,660
there's still...

939
00:51:38,020 --> 00:51:40,460
one more thing we haven't done.

940
00:51:40,660 --> 00:51:41,800
What?

941
00:51:52,970 --> 00:51:56,110
Gosh, this is so embarrassing.
What am I even doing?

942
00:51:57,910 --> 00:51:58,910
Oh, my.

943
00:52:03,080 --> 00:52:04,250
Are you crying?

944
00:52:05,790 --> 00:52:08,050
No, don't cry. This isn't the time.

945
00:52:08,560 --> 00:52:09,590
If you cry, I'm leaving.

946
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:11,590
- I'm going to leave!
- No.

947
00:52:16,900 --> 00:52:17,930
Of course not.

948
00:52:21,070 --> 00:52:22,570
I'm not that...

949
00:52:24,570 --> 00:52:25,970
pathetic.

950
00:52:51,300 --> 00:52:53,530
(Ham Ji Woo Solo Concert)

951
00:52:59,640 --> 00:53:01,010
I can't take this.

952
00:53:15,560 --> 00:53:20,090
<i>In a corner of the dawn sky</i>

953
00:53:21,390 --> 00:53:26,000
<i>Suddenly, a shooting star appears</i>

954
00:53:26,270 --> 00:53:29,140
<i>And in the blink of an eye</i>

955
00:53:29,340 --> 00:53:32,010
<i>Right above my head</i>

956
00:53:32,310 --> 00:53:37,340
<i>Pouring down like rain</i>

957
00:53:37,840 --> 00:53:42,450
<i>Oh, what a beautiful day</i>

958
00:53:42,680 --> 00:53:47,120
<i>Even the sun and the moon</i>
<i>are on my side</i>

959
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:49,590
<i>Shining just for me</i>

960
00:53:49,590 --> 00:53:54,190
<i>Oh, be my salvation</i>

961
00:53:54,590 --> 00:53:58,770
<i>In my empty heart</i>

962
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:04,270
<i>It's full of stars</i>

963
00:54:07,210 --> 00:54:09,510
<i>You're my xylophone</i>

964
00:54:09,510 --> 00:54:11,980
<i>You're my ding-dong-daeng</i>

965
00:54:12,250 --> 00:54:16,420
<i>If it makes you happy</i>
<i>I could be a trainee every day</i>

966
00:54:16,550 --> 00:54:18,820
<i>You're my xylophone</i>

967
00:54:18,820 --> 00:54:20,750
<i>You're my ding-dong-daeng</i>

968
00:54:20,750 --> 00:54:24,060
<i>You make me sing</i>

969
00:54:25,790 --> 00:54:31,970
<i>I can't erase that feeling</i>

970
00:54:31,970 --> 00:54:37,570
<i>I'm dizzy</i>
<i>like a shimmering heat haze</i>

971
00:54:37,570 --> 00:54:43,280
<i>My faltering steps always before you</i>

972
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:48,720
<i>I'm so dizzy, I'm reeling</i>

973
00:54:55,990 --> 00:55:00,860
<i>On this long and winding road</i>

974
00:55:01,830 --> 00:55:05,600
<i>My weary heart</i>

975
00:55:06,170 --> 00:55:08,970
<i>Searched for a place to rest</i>

976
00:55:10,000 --> 00:55:14,240
<i>Letting out a sigh</i>

977
00:55:15,010 --> 00:55:18,180
<i>On that lonely night</i>

978
00:55:20,280 --> 00:55:25,150
<i>Like a warm and gentle greeting</i>

979
00:55:25,850 --> 00:55:30,660
<i>You're the one I still long for</i>

980
00:55:31,520 --> 00:55:33,790
I'm done trying harder!

981
00:55:34,160 --> 00:55:37,430
<i>With you, all right?</i>

982
00:55:38,730 --> 00:55:41,130
Jung Da Hae.
You have more than I do.

983
00:55:41,830 --> 00:55:44,540
So don't avoid me.

984
00:55:46,510 --> 00:55:47,910
So now you're being punished.

985
00:55:52,780 --> 00:55:54,250
You, Dr. Ham,

986
00:55:54,250 --> 00:55:57,780
dreaming of you is a special treat
I have to save up for these days.

987
00:56:00,850 --> 00:56:03,420
Will you marry me?

988
00:56:27,550 --> 00:56:28,650
So, what did you think?

989
00:56:29,680 --> 00:56:32,190
I thought it was even better live
than the studio version.

990
00:56:34,190 --> 00:56:37,160
Well, yes. I liked it.

991
00:56:39,090 --> 00:56:40,790
If you did,
why didn't you get married?

992
00:56:42,200 --> 00:56:43,230
Excuse me?

993
00:56:44,060 --> 00:56:46,170
I was so curious to see
what you looked like.

994
00:56:47,130 --> 00:56:48,330
And now I finally get to meet you.

995
00:56:50,070 --> 00:56:52,910
- Are you perhaps...
- Ji Woo finally seems happy.

996
00:56:54,510 --> 00:56:56,110
And I think it's all thanks to you.

997
00:56:58,380 --> 00:56:59,410
Thank you.

998
00:57:04,820 --> 00:57:05,850
Wait...

999
00:57:22,000 --> 00:57:23,270
Hey, Ji Song.

1000
00:57:23,370 --> 00:57:26,540
Da Hae! I just heard from Eun Sang.

1001
00:57:35,280 --> 00:57:37,720
I will use the driver from now on
when I hit you.

1002
00:57:43,920 --> 00:57:45,360
A fan of yours gave you this.

1003
00:57:47,760 --> 00:57:48,930
What is this?

1004
00:57:58,640 --> 00:58:00,940
You're the leading man now.

1005
00:58:01,440 --> 00:58:04,140
Congratulations.
I'll always be rooting for you.

1006
00:58:08,480 --> 00:58:11,020
(Small Theater)

1007
00:58:28,530 --> 00:58:29,600
Hey, guys.

1008
00:58:30,100 --> 00:58:33,110
This morning, I couldn't get
the lid off the strawberry jam,

1009
00:58:33,370 --> 00:58:35,510
and I almost popped my own lid.

1010
00:58:35,840 --> 00:58:36,840
But then...

1011
00:58:41,610 --> 00:58:44,050
Sweetheart, when did you
get so strong?

1012
00:58:44,120 --> 00:58:46,320
From eating and playing a lot.

1013
00:58:47,420 --> 00:58:49,320
Where could you play? It's so cold.

1014
00:58:49,590 --> 00:58:52,060
It must be freezing where you are.

1015
00:58:52,430 --> 00:58:54,790
What? What are you
talking about, Mom?

1016
00:58:54,990 --> 00:58:56,560
Spring came a long time ago.

1017
00:58:57,100 --> 00:58:58,560
The whole world is full of spring.

1018
00:58:58,970 --> 00:59:00,030
What?

1019
00:59:12,550 --> 00:59:15,880
You cried so much, Mom,
that all the ice melted away.

1020
00:59:17,650 --> 00:59:18,680
Ji Sang...

1021
00:59:22,220 --> 00:59:23,690
It's warm now, Mom.

1022
00:59:24,320 --> 00:59:26,360
So you should go out
and have fun now, Mom.

1023
00:59:26,760 --> 00:59:28,590
See? Go on out and play.

1024
00:59:31,730 --> 00:59:33,030
That's when I realized.

1025
00:59:33,470 --> 00:59:36,600
That maybe my grief
had started to fade.

1026
00:59:38,140 --> 00:59:41,210
And that maybe, I could start over.

1027
00:59:44,940 --> 00:59:48,450
So with that in mind, I'm thinking
we could have some fun again.

1028
00:59:49,280 --> 00:59:51,280
What should we name
our new playground?

1029
00:59:51,680 --> 00:59:52,820
- Ji Song.
- Eun Sang Town?

1030
00:59:52,820 --> 00:59:54,350
- Da Hae.
- Ji Sang Villa?

1031
00:59:55,390 --> 00:59:57,520
Or what about Average Street?

1032
00:59:58,620 --> 01:00:00,830
Honestly, I haven't picked a name,

1033
01:00:02,030 --> 01:00:04,630
so let's take our time
and build it together.

1034
01:00:06,200 --> 01:00:08,400
So guys, come on over and play.

1035
01:00:17,940 --> 01:00:20,680
Ji Song, did you bring
the rent money?

1036
01:00:23,280 --> 01:00:24,350
Da Hae.

1037
01:00:25,720 --> 01:00:28,750
- Eun Sang!
- Eun Sang!

1038
01:00:29,490 --> 01:00:31,060
Eun Sang is back.

1039
01:00:32,590 --> 01:00:34,590
I missed you.

1040
01:00:43,000 --> 01:00:44,070
How was it?

1041
01:00:44,370 --> 01:00:45,640
Did you have a good time?

1042
01:00:47,210 --> 01:00:48,980
I cried my heart out.

1043
01:00:49,510 --> 01:00:50,840
Are you feeling better now?

1044
01:00:52,780 --> 01:00:53,910
I'm okay.

1045
01:00:55,720 --> 01:00:56,880
I want to be okay.

1046
01:00:58,580 --> 01:00:59,650
But...

1047
01:01:00,420 --> 01:01:04,420
some grief is meant to be unpacked
a little at a time, over a lifetime.

1048
01:01:11,800 --> 01:01:13,130
What about you two?

1049
01:01:13,530 --> 01:01:15,870
Has life changed at all
after you made money?

1050
01:01:16,240 --> 01:01:19,170
Well, as they say,
money makes money.

1051
01:01:19,670 --> 01:01:21,670
Our shop is the most popular one
in the neighborhood.

1052
01:01:23,010 --> 01:01:25,510
- Maybe I should raise the rent.
- No.

1053
01:01:27,910 --> 01:01:29,980
I'm pretty much the same.

1054
01:01:30,580 --> 01:01:33,920
I eat, work, sleep,
and rest now and then.

1055
01:01:34,550 --> 01:01:36,190
I deal with people's drama.

1056
01:01:38,120 --> 01:01:40,760
But after making money,

1057
01:01:41,130 --> 01:01:44,360
I feel like I have the strength
to look forward to tomorrow.

1058
01:01:44,660 --> 01:01:45,930
Yes.

1059
01:01:46,100 --> 01:01:48,800
Lately, I get excited for
what each new day will bring.

1060
01:01:50,840 --> 01:01:53,710
Are you sure it's just tomorrow
you're looking forward to?

1061
01:01:54,670 --> 01:01:55,840
Is it just tomorrow?

1062
01:01:56,740 --> 01:01:57,740
Come on.

1063
01:01:59,750 --> 01:02:01,810
What are you talking about?
Seriously.

1064
01:02:01,880 --> 01:02:02,980
- Are you sure it's just tomorrow...
- Let's ask again.

1065
01:02:02,980 --> 01:02:04,120
you're looking forward to?

1066
01:02:07,090 --> 01:02:08,350
Hey, didn't you two break up?

1067
01:02:08,650 --> 01:02:10,820
- Should I just say it?
- You don't have to.

1068
01:02:13,730 --> 01:02:14,960
Yes, sir.

1069
01:02:15,360 --> 01:02:16,960
Yes, the seminar went well.

1070
01:02:18,360 --> 01:02:20,270
No, I'm heading out from here.

1071
01:02:20,270 --> 01:02:21,700
I have somewhere to stop by.

1072
01:02:24,070 --> 01:02:25,240
Just because.

1073
01:02:25,740 --> 01:02:27,770
Maybe because I need
a little mental reset?

1074
01:03:18,860 --> 01:03:19,860
What?

1075
01:03:27,970 --> 01:03:28,970
You...

1076
01:03:30,400 --> 01:03:31,970
You really are a piece of work,
aren't you?

1077
01:03:32,570 --> 01:03:36,010
- Dr. Ham.
- After a year, you'd just leave?

1078
01:03:37,140 --> 01:03:39,810
Something came up that day.

1079
01:03:41,110 --> 01:03:43,850
But I didn't just disappear.
I left you a card.

1080
01:03:43,850 --> 01:03:45,450
Leaving a lingering note like that?

1081
01:03:45,920 --> 01:03:48,290
I seriously thought we were over.

1082
01:03:48,490 --> 01:03:51,990
I thought we were leads in a movie
with an open ending.

1083
01:03:52,060 --> 01:03:53,330
No, what are you talking about?

1084
01:03:54,530 --> 01:03:55,860
I just...

1085
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:59,570
Like you rooted for me, Dr. Ham,
I wanted to do the same for you.

1086
01:04:18,450 --> 01:04:21,720
Why are you about to cry?
I missed you so much.

1087
01:04:24,960 --> 01:04:25,990
Liar.

1088
01:04:28,060 --> 01:04:29,160
It's true.

1089
01:04:30,400 --> 01:04:32,100
I wanted to call you overseas
every single night.

1090
01:04:32,670 --> 01:04:34,570
Do you have any idea how hard
I had to fight that urge?

1091
01:04:38,200 --> 01:04:39,270
No, can't say I do.

1092
01:04:39,770 --> 01:04:41,040
And plane tickets...

1093
01:04:41,310 --> 01:04:44,610
Every day, I'd get to the buy button
and barely stop myself.

1094
01:04:44,610 --> 01:04:46,850
- Do you get it now?
- And I'm telling you, I didn't.

1095
01:04:47,310 --> 01:04:49,220
You have no idea
how much I missed you.

1096
01:04:49,720 --> 01:04:51,680
It got so bad
I started seeing things.

1097
01:04:53,490 --> 01:04:56,660
I thought I was going crazy
from studying too hard.

1098
01:04:58,760 --> 01:04:59,860
What's with you?

1099
01:05:00,460 --> 01:05:03,260
I'm over here pouring my heart out
about how much I missed you,

1100
01:05:03,530 --> 01:05:05,100
and you give me nothing.

1101
01:05:07,270 --> 01:05:09,840
Why aren't you saying anything?
You're making me nervous.

1102
01:05:10,640 --> 01:05:12,510
Maybe it's because
you're talking too much?

1103
01:05:13,570 --> 01:05:14,570
Excuse me?

1104
01:05:40,400 --> 01:05:41,730
So, your ambition...

1105
01:05:41,970 --> 01:05:43,370
Have you fulfilled it all?

1106
01:05:44,300 --> 01:05:45,570
And your dream...

1107
01:05:46,570 --> 01:05:47,770
Did you achieve it?

1108
01:05:49,210 --> 01:05:50,380
No.

1109
01:05:51,610 --> 01:05:52,850
There's one I haven't fulfilled yet.

1110
01:05:55,680 --> 01:05:56,980
You, Dr. Ham.

1111
01:05:57,780 --> 01:05:59,190
You...

1112
01:06:00,090 --> 01:06:02,520
are the one dream I've been saving.

1113
01:06:04,190 --> 01:06:05,260
So...

1114
01:06:06,830 --> 01:06:09,090
let me keep on dreaming.

1115
01:06:12,970 --> 01:06:14,130
Well, then...

1116
01:06:18,240 --> 01:06:19,610
Why don't you put this on?

1117
01:06:50,900 --> 01:06:51,970
I love you,

1118
01:06:52,540 --> 01:06:53,570
Ham Ji Woo.

1119
01:07:45,390 --> 01:07:46,690
A story like this one.

1120
01:07:46,990 --> 01:07:52,560
So, how should the story
of those who desired more end?

1121
01:07:54,800 --> 01:07:56,900
Being punished for their greed,

1122
01:07:57,240 --> 01:07:59,340
would a bad ending like that
be natural?

1123
01:07:59,840 --> 01:08:02,240
Life never goes the way you expect,

1124
01:08:02,470 --> 01:08:06,050
and we're ready to enjoy
even its unpredictable moments.

1125
01:08:07,110 --> 01:08:09,780
So I'd call this a happy ending
for everyone.

1126
01:08:10,080 --> 01:08:11,650
And why not?

1127
01:08:12,280 --> 01:08:13,550
Don't we have that opening event
next week?

1128
01:08:13,620 --> 01:08:14,820
Aren't you taking it a bit too easy?

1129
01:08:15,250 --> 01:08:16,260
Gosh, it's so bitter.

1130
01:08:17,290 --> 01:08:18,320
And sour.

1131
01:08:18,990 --> 01:08:20,330
That's weird.

1132
01:08:20,390 --> 01:08:23,160
Why do I get a bad feeling
from its smell?

1133
01:08:25,160 --> 01:08:26,570
Coffee's supposed to be bitter.

1134
01:08:26,700 --> 01:08:28,500
Just drink what you're given.

1135
01:08:29,470 --> 01:08:30,500
Mr. Ko Dae Young.

1136
01:08:30,770 --> 01:08:32,240
Yes, boss.

1137
01:08:33,340 --> 01:08:35,010
- Wait, I thought he was the boss.
- I don't know who's who anymore.

1138
01:08:35,070 --> 01:08:36,510
What can I get for you?

1139
01:08:40,450 --> 01:08:41,650
Make me another one.

1140
01:08:41,980 --> 01:08:43,920
One that's tastier and more popular.

1141
01:08:43,920 --> 01:08:44,920
Basically,

1142
01:08:44,920 --> 01:08:47,490
- a better one!
- A better one!

1143
01:09:07,210 --> 01:09:10,180
(To the Moon)

1144
01:10:46,640 --> 01:10:52,140
(Thank you for watching
and supporting To the Moon.)

1145
01:10:52,140 --> 01:10:57,250
(We will root for your journey
to your own moon as well.)

1146
01:11:01,520 --> 01:11:03,560
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
